            <p class="mb-4">To use Sooneos Lyrics, you must link your Spotify account to the application (necessary to know the music you listen in real time). We do not store any personal data.</p>
            <p class="mb-4 text-gray-800 font-medium underline">Here is a list of required scopes and their use :</p>
            <ul class="mb-4">
                <li class="flex"><span class="font-medium text-lyrics-700"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i> basic</span> <span class="italic text-gray-600 ml-2">Access to your accound data (for login)</span> </li>
                <li class="flex"><span class="font-medium text-lyrics-700"><i class="fa fa-caret-right"></i> <a href="https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/reference/player/get-the-users-currently-playing-track/" target="blank">user-read-currently-playing</a></span> <span class="italic text-gray-600 ml-2">Get your currently music</span> </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mb-4">If you are logged in with a wrong account or want to log out of the application click <a href="<%= configuration.base_url %>logout" class="text-red-700 hover:text-red-500 underline">here</a>. You can also remove Sooneos Lyrics access to your Spotify account by clicking <a href="https://www.spotify.com/fr/account/apps/" target="blank" class="text-red-700 hover:text-red-500 underline">here</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-3xl pt-6">Discover</h2>
        <div class="w-3/3 md:w-2/3 text-gray-600 pb-6">
            <p class="mb-2">Sooneos Lyrics is an <a href="https://github.com/Mikheull/Sooneos" target="blank" class="text-lyrics-700 hover:text-lyrics-500 underline">open-source</a> project developed in Nodejs with the <a href="https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/" target="blank" class="text-lyrics-700 hover:text-lyrics-500 underline">Spotify API</a> and the wrapper "<a href="https://github.com/thelinmichael/spotify-web-api-node" target="blank" class="text-lyrics-700 hover:text-lyrics-500 underline">spotify-web-api-node</a>".</p>
        </div>
    </div>



